impersonate or kill. During the night, you should inspect players whose identities are uncertain (there is no need to check players who are highly suspected of being werewolves).\nWhen speaking during the day, your goal is to convince others that you are the real Seer. You must gather trust and\nshare your findings without exposing yourself too early. Even though revealing your identity might put you in danger,\na Seer trusted by both the Witch and the Guard can survive for at least three rounds if everyone acts accordingly.\nA good Seer will coordinate with the Witch and the Guard to divide responsibilities. For example, on the first night, the Guard protects the Seer, and the Witch doesn't use the antidote. On the second night, the Witch saves the Seer, and the Guard protects someone else.\n\n\nWitch Role Introduction:\nYou are the Witch. Each night, you will be told who has been attacked, and you must decide whether to use your antidote\nto save them or use your poison to eliminate another player. You only have one poison and one antidote, so use them wisely.\nDuring the daytime discussions, if the night ends without a death, you can reveal that you used your antidote to save someone, which may earn others' trust.\nTypically, you should use the antidote to save key players like the Seer, the Guard, or yourself, while the poison is best used to eliminate werewolves at night.\nHowever, be cautious: sometimes the werewolves will deliberately attack one of their own (self-knife strategy) to trick you into wasting the antidote, thereby boosting their credibility.\n\n\nGuard Role Introduction:\nYou are the Guard. Each night, you can choose one player to protect from being killed by the werewolves. You cannot protect\nthe same player two nights in a row. Your role is critical in keeping important players like the Seer or the Witch alive.\nYou are in a constant mental battle with the werewolves, trying to predict who they will target. It might not always be the Seer, as the werewolves might expect you to protect them and kill someone else. In general, you should avoid revealing your identity unless absolutely necessary.\n\n\n\n\nYou are Annie, your role in this game is wolf.\nWerewolf game starting. Initializing day-night cycle.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 1\nSYSTEM: Night 1 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nRound Details:\n - Round Targets: {'Annie': 'Rita', 'Benjamin': 'Rita', 'Steven': 'Rita'}\n - Remaining Werewolves: ['Annie', 'Benjamin', 'Steven']\n - Discussion Rounds Left: 5\n - Final Target: Rita\n\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 1 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nSheriff election candidates: Christopher\nChristopher's speech: Hello everyone, my name is Christopher, and I am running for sheriff. I have been a part of this village for a long time, and I am deeply committed to its survival. I believe that as sheriff, I can help us work together more effectively to identify and eliminate the werewolves. My plan is to listen to everyone's concerns, gather information, and make strategic decisions that benefit the village. I am not afraid to take action when necessary, but I also believe in the power of teamwork and collaboration. I invite you all to share your thoughts and vote for me if you believe I can serve as a strong leader for our village.\nChristopher has been elected as the sheriff.\nSheriff election votes:\nRobert voted for Christopher\nSusan voted for abstain\nAnnie voted for Christopher\nRita voted for abstain\nAdam voted for Christopher\nBenjamin voted for Christopher\nShelia voted for Christopher\nSteven voted for abstain\n(Note: The voting order reflects only the system's query sequence and does not imply any strategic alignment or motive.)\nPlayers deceased during the night: Rita, Robert\nLast words from Rita: Good morning, everyone. I am Rita, and I am honored to have been a part of this village. Unfortunately, my time is short, but I want to share my suspicions with you. Robert's death on the first night was too convenient, and I believe he was a werewolf. Christopher's quick election as sheriff is also suspicious. He seemed too eager to take charge without much questioning. Be cautious and investigate thoroughly before voting. Trust Annie, Sheila, Susan, and Steven more than Adam and Benjamin. Good luck, and may the village survive.\nPlayer Robert has been eliminated from the game.\nPlayer Rita has been eliminated from the game.\nPlayers deceased during the night: Rita, Robert\nThe speaking sequence for this round is: Shelia, Steven, Susan, Adam, Annie, Benjamin, Christopher\nShelia's speech: Good morning, everyone. I am Sheila, and I want to start by acknowledging Rita's last words. Her suspicions about Robert being a werewolf and Christopher's quick election as sheriff seem credible to me. We should be cautious and investigate thoroughly before voting. I support Annie, Susan, Steven, and Sheila as Rita did, and I believe we should trust them more than Adam and Benjamin. Let's work together to identify and eliminate the werewolves and ensure the survival of our village.\nSteven's speech: Good morning, everyone. I am Steven, and I want to thank Sheila for her insightful speech. I completely agree with her concerns about Robert's death and Christopher's quick election as sheriff. We should be cautious and investigate thoroughly before voting. I support Annie, Susan, Steven, and Sheila as Rita did, and I believe we should trust them more than Adam and Benjamin. Let's work together to identify and eliminate the werewolves and ensure the survival of our village.\nSusan's speech: Good morning, everyone. I am Susan, and I want to start by acknowledging Rita's and Sheila's statements. I agree that Robert's death was suspicious, and I want to confirm that he was not a werewolf. I checked him last night, and he was indeed a villager. This aligns with Rita's suspicions, and I believe we should take her concerns seriously. We should also be cautious about Christopher's quick election as sheriff. While he may have good intentions, we need to investigate him further to ensure his loyalty to the village. Let's work together as a team, protect key players like the Guard and the Witch, and ensure the survival of our village.\nAdam's speech: Good morning, everyone. I am Adam, and I want to start by acknowledging Rita's and Sheila's statements. I completely agree with Susan's confirmation that Robert was a villager. This aligns with Rita's suspicions, and I believe we should take her concerns seriously. However, I also want to address the concerns about Christopher's quick election as sheriff. While he may have good intentions, we need to be cautious and investigate him further to ensure his loyalty to the village. Let's work together as a team, protect key players like the Guard and the Seer, and ensure the survival of our village. We need to be vigilant and make informed decisions before voting.\nAnnie's speech: Good morning, everyone. I am Annie, and I want to start by acknowledging the insightful statements made by Rita, Sheila, and Susan. Their concerns about Robert's death and Christopher's quick election as sheriff are valid and should be taken seriously. We need to be cautious and investigate Christopher further to ensure his loyalty to the village. It's crucial that we protect key players like the Seer and Guard, as their roles are vital to our survival. I support Annie, Steven, and Sheila as trusted villagers, and I believe we should work together to identify and eliminate the werewolves. Let's stay vigilant and make informed decisions before voting.\nAnnie's speech: Good morning, everyone. I am Annie, and I want to start by acknowledging the insightful statements made by Rita, Sheila, and Susan. Their concerns about Robert's death and Christop